      "writtenOn": "2026-07-10T09:44:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Apologizes for the confusing statement. That was the previous design which I have abandoned.\nI have updated the document in PS8 and there should be no parent object anymore.\nThe reason I abandon this is because I just noticed the design was against the sensor-architecture stated in the following link:\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/6dfd3bb55bcb827d38ce6ce11b84913596aa23ca/architecture/sensor-architecture.md?plain\u003d1#L19\n\nThe design proposal in PS8 uses flattened approaches to expose the state set/component sensor as a single dbus-object similar to numeric sensor.\n\nIn addition, the `\u003clabel\u003e` in component state sensor has a slightly different naming rule compared to numeric sensor otherwise there could be naming conflict in the case where a composite state sensor having multiple component sensor with identical state set type.",
      "parentUuid": "8458bc3a_2c35418a",
